long_desc.thetext:
It would be nice to have a property for tables similar to maxHeight,called maxRowsDisplayed or something, that would make it easier to set the max height depending on the number of rows displayed.

Currently, one way to achieve this would be:

// resize handling
table.getPaneScroller(0).getChildControl("pane").addListener("paneUpdated", function() {
  var headerHeight = table.getPaneScroller(0).getChildControl("header").getBounds().height;
  var statusbarHeight = table.getChildControl("statusbar").getBounds().height;
  var height = table.getTableModel().getRowCount() * table.getRowHeight() + headerHeight + statusbarHeight;
  table.setHeight(height);
}, this);

It would be much nicer to be able to instead do something like:

table.setMaxRowsDisplayed(table.getTableModel().getRowCount());


Context: http://comments.gmane.org/gmane.comp.lang.javascript.qooxdoo.devel/39143
